Day of Sun and February 16 to Be Commemorated in Guyana 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The Guyanese preparatory committee for commemorating the Day of the Sun and February 16 was inaugurated with due ceremony in Georgetown on Jan. 31.
 At the ceremony Deputy Mayor of Georgetown Robert Williams, who is chairman of the Guyana National Committee for the Development of the Friendship Relations with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee decided to set a commemoration period from February to April and hold various events such as a seminar on the Juche idea and a film show during the period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted there.

DPRK Joint Statement Favored in Switzerland 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The Swiss Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea issued a statement on Feb. 2 in support of the joint statement of the political parties, government and organizations of the DPRK.
 The statement said that the independent and peaceful reunification of Korea would be accelerated when all the Koreans decisively reject cooperation with outsiders and give priority to the interests of the nation, transcending their differences in ideology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the hope that the political parties and organizations in south Korea would affirmatively accept the joint statement and fully support the north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It held that the south Korean authorities, too, should work for the national independence and the independent reunification of Korea, getting out of the U.S. control.

Abrogation of NSL Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The Family Movement for Realizing Democracy in south Korea reportedly held the 651st Thursday meeting in Seoul on Feb. 1, at which it declared that it would fight out for the abrogation of the "National Security Law."
 Speakers at the meeting referred to the fact that the security authorities, who would fake up all sorts of "cases," recently searched the house of Ri Si U, a media-person, charging that he "gave away a state secret." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such reckless suppression of Ri who has worked for peace is attributable to the NSL, an evil law of the times that is still left intact, they said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They held that the security mechanism should be dissolved without fail as it is used only to imprison pro-reunification patriots and democrats.

Struggle against GNP Staged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- A press conference denouncing the "Grand National Party," a descendant of Chun Doo Hwan, was reportedly called in front of the GNP building in Seoul on Feb. 2 under the sponsorship of the South Kyongsang Provincial Measure Committee of south Korea against "Ilhae Park."
 Asking what Chun Doo Hwan, the chief culprit of the May 18 Kwangju Massacre, had done, the speakers stressed that they would never allow the moves of the GNP to repeat the history of bloodbath. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then, a statement denouncing the GNP was read out at the press conference. It said that if the GNP connives at the case of "Ilhae Park," the people would wage a decisive resistance against it which is branded as a party defiling the people and committing crimes against ethics and a party seeking to restore the "5th Republic." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the press conference, members of civic and public organizations including the measure committee struggled to have an interview with the representative of the GNP to convey a written protest to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They staged a demonstration.

Magazine "Korea Information" Released in Sweden 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The Sweden-Korea Friendship Association released the first issue of magazine "Korea Information."
 The magazine edited articles on the Day of the Sun, February 16 and the Army Day of the DPRK under the title "Greatest holidays of the Korean people in 2007." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In an article under the sub-title "95th Birth Anniversary of President Kim Il Sung" it praised him as the father of socialist Korea and the founder of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An article sub-titled "Birthday of HE Kim Jong Il" stressed that the Korean people, led by him, have reliably defended the sovereignty of the country, waging a dynamic struggle to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation under the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In an article under the sub-title "75th Anniversary of the Korean People's Army" the magazine said that the KPA is the powerful armed forces winning victory after victory under the banner of Songun. It introduced in details the facts that Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il had strengthened and developed the Korean revolutionary armed forces into invincible ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the titles "Korea is ushering in a new heyday, confident of victory" and "All the Korean people are ardently called upon to achieve their alliance for reunification" it carried the contents of the DPRK's joint New Year editorial and the joint statement of the political parties, government and organizations of the DPRK and edited articles introducing the situation of the Korean Peninsula.

Film Show and Friendship Meeting 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The Ministry of Culture arranged a film show and a friendship meeting at the People's Palace of Culture on Tuesday for officials in charge of cultural relations of foreign embassies here on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il.
 Present there were Vice-Minister Jo Chan Gu and officials of the ministry and movie men. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants watched the Korean feature film "Photo Left by Him." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed a friendship meeting.

Reception Given for Chinese Embassy Officials
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The International Department of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea arranged a reception at the Pyongyang Koryo Hotel on Tuesday for the staff members of the Chinese embassy here on the occasion of the New Year, Juche 96 (2007).
 Present on invitation were Ambassador Liu Xiaoming and staff members of the Chinese embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Vice-Director Kim Thae Jong and officials of the International Department of the WPK Central Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Military Attaches Corps Visits Kim Il Sung Military University
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The Military Attaches Corps here visited Kim Il Sung Military University on Tuesday on the occasion of the February holiday.
 The members of the corps first laid a bouquet before the statue of President Kim Il Sung at the university and paid respects to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the visitors went round various educational facilities, being briefed on the fact that under the wise guidance of Kim Il Sung and Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il the university has trained many competent military commanding officers equipped with the Juche-based military idea and war methods and contributed to the strengthening of the Korean revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Xilian, military, naval and air attache of the Chinese embassy who is doyen of the corps, said that Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il have worked heart and soul to increase the national defence capability of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The university with modern educational equipment and educators of ability is turning out many competent military commanding officers, he said, wishing the Korean People's Army success in increasing the national defence capability under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Military Attache of the Iranian embassy Abdullah Jalali Nasab noted that Korea is a small country, but it is courageously standing against the United States. The KPA will always win in the fight with any imperialists, he said.

Japan's Dangerous Scheme to Build New Support System for War under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- Japanese Prime Minister Abe some time ago addressed a joint session of both houses, setting out the policy orientation and targets for this year, in which he elaborated on the need to "revise the constitution." Viewing this as a clear indication that the goal of his Cabinet is nothing but militarization peculiar to Japan, a by-lined article of Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says:
  The Abe Cabinet is pitching for turning Japan into a state pursuing a war under the flowery signboard of building "a beautiful country." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It, to begin with, is going to change the present state system into a wartime system for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese militarist forces revived under the aegis of the U.S. imperialists have long sought to replace the state system based on the "pacifist constitution" with one allowing lawful aggression overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years, the Japanese reactionary ruling camp has become more outspoken in their push for completely changing the state system into a wartime system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Abe in his Diet speech waxed eloquent, blaring that "it is now time to embark anew and boldly revise the postwar regime by going back to the starting point," and it was his "mission to draw up a new national image for Japan." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Abe Cabinet intends to reshape the state structure after the U.S. pattern to subordinate it to the moves for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Defense Agency has been upgraded to Defense Ministry in the Abe Cabinet. This is a big step toward the building of a state pursuing a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now it is going to scrap the "pacifist constitution" in a bid to make Japan a war-oriented state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The word "pacifist" could be attached to the present constitution of Japan because Article 9 of it bans possession of war capability and war itself. The Japanese reactionary ruling camp is going to get rid of such basic provisions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Abe group is working to create a social climate favorable for bringing a war-oriented state into shape by inculcating militarist idea into the minds of the Japanese people in real earnest. It is only too natural that the world is heightening vigilance against the militarization maneuvers of the Japanese reactionaries.

U.S. Accused of Patronizing Japan's Distortion of History
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The United States is now openly using as an English textbook for middle school students in all its regions a historical novel of Japan which shamelessly distorts the history of aggression of Japan and insults the Korean nation. This book is said to have been distributed in some foreigners' schools in south Korea, too.
 Commenting on this, a Rodong Sinmun analyst Wednesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an intolerable mockery of and insult to the Korean nation and a very nefarious act trampling upon justice and praising the history of injustice for the U.S. to allow itself to use the novel distorting history as a middle school textbook, in which the reactionaries of Japan maliciously slander the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for the autobiographical novel which is said to have been written by a daughter of a Japanese war criminal who was eleven years old when the Japanese imperialists were defeated, it is full of lies and fabrication utterly inconsistent with the then historical environment and facts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. must know that Japan kept Korea under their military occupation and brutal and harsh colonial fascist repressive rule unparalleled in history for over 40 years. Nevertheless, the U.S. is openly using the blatantly distorted history book of Japan, which was written by an offspring of a war criminal. This reveals its intention to bury in oblivion the bloody past crimes of the islanders and use them as a shock brigade of aggression and war by misleading public opinion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All this proves irrefutably that the U.S. and Japan are dangerous accomplices and conspirators in the hostile policies against the DPRK and aggressive moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The criminal acts of Japan insulting the Korean nation and brazenly distorting history and the U.S. imperialists zealously singing duet with them can never be overlooked.

Study Tour Made of Revolutionary Battle Sites and Historic Sites in Mt. Paektu Area
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Samjiyon, February 6 (KCNA) -- A group of youths and children from all parts of the country for the study tour of the old home in the secret camp in Mt. Paektu went round the revolutionary battle sites and historic sites in Mt. Paektu area from Feb. 1 to 6 on the threshold of February 16, the greatest national holiday.
 The members of the group placed floral baskets and bouquets before the statues of President Kim Il Sung at the Pochonbo Revolutionary Battle Site and on the shore of Lake Samji before making bows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While visiting the Pochonbo Revolutionary Battle Site, the members of the study tour group deeply grasped the gifted tactics and wisdom of Kim Il Sung, going round the then historic command post of the Pochonbo battle, police post of the Japanese imperialists, sub-county administration office and other battle sites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They reached the secret camp in Mt. Paektu through Posori spring, Junghung tableland, Phothae revolutionary historic site and Rimyongsu revolutionary historic site. In front of the old home in the secret camp they held an oath-taking meeting of youths and children from all parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After leaving the secret camp the marchers arrived at Lake Samji associated with immortal revolutionary feats of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were briefed on the Samjiyon Grand Monument before looking round groups of sculptures depicting the boundless reverence of the anti-Japanese guerrillas and people for Kim Il Sung, their indomitable fighting spirit and ardent patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they visited buildings of the Songun era erected in the township of Samjiyon County including the Paektu Museum and Samjiyon Schoolchildren�fs Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the tour they had question-and-answer contests on the joint editorial for this year and the brilliant revolutionary history of the Workers' Party of Korea and a contest of singing revolutionary songs in chorus while marching in array, sports games, recreation party and other political and cultural events.

New Program "Oryon" Made in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The Information Center under Kim Il Sung University has made a new program "Oryon" (Version 1.0). It arouses interest among people.
 It is a kind of paduk (go) game program, in which one can play paduk with black and white stones. He or she, who puts five stones on the paduk board abreast vertical, horizontal or oblique line, in advance of his or her opposite, wins the game. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One can choose any grade of game for beginner, intermediate or expert, by clicking a relevant picture in the setting dialog-box. Everybody from the beginner to amateur can easily understand it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the program gives the users virtual feeling with the introduction of the real-time image processing technology, new search engine and sounds. It not only helps children develop their intelligence but also contributes to the cultural and emotional life of the people.

Sports Contest for Paektusan Cup Closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- The 12th Sports Contest for Paektusan Cup of officials of national institutions, which opened on Jan. 23 on the threshold of the February 16, closed with due ceremony at the Basketball Gymnasium in Chongchun Street here on Wednesday.
 The contest was held divided into four groups. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first place in total points of the contest was taken respectively by the State Planning Commission, the Mansudae Art Studio, the Koryo Public Service Guidance Bureau and the Central Bank, which have conducted sports activities on a popular and normal basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony were Secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea Kim Jung Rin, Vice-Premier Kwak Pom Gi and leading officials of commissions, ministries and national institutions and government employees and players. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cups, citations and medals were awarded to the units and players that proved successful in the contest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the C.C., the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, made a closing address there.

National Fine Art Exhibition Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- A national fine art exhibition was opened at the Korean Art Gallery here on Wednesday to celebrate February 16.
 Put on display there are more than 500 fine art pieces of rich ideological content and high artistry. They truthfully depicted the revolutionary exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and their personality as peerlessly great persons and the national pride and honor of the army and people of the DPRK who hold Kim Jong Il in high esteem as their benevolent father. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are Korean painting "Front at night", oil painting "30 millions of people should be under arms" and sculpture "Always believing in the people", which arouse viewers' deep reverence and longing for President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are also Korean paintings "Calling them proud scenes of the Songun era", "I missed my soldiers" and "Long journey for happiness" and oil painting "Our general visits land of Samsu" that vividly portrayed the immortal feats and the noble popular traits of Kim Jong Il who has made a long journey of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also displayed are fine art pieces showing the brilliant life of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at its opening ceremony were artists and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minister of Culture Kang Nung Su made an opening address. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  On the same day, a central fine art show was opened.

Sinister Intention of Japanese Reactionaries in Suppressing Chongryon Debunked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- What the Japanese reactionaries seek in their hysteric suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan is to aggravate the DPRK-Japan relations by getting on the nerve of the DPRK by persecuting Koreans in Japan and suppressing Chongryon to destroy it and, with this as a pretext, justify their clamorous sanctions and pressure upon the DPRK and realize their ambition to stage a comeback to Korea, notes Minju Joson in a news analysis Wednesday.
  The analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The suppression of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan should be regarded as a token of the ill-will and moral vulgarity of the Samurai clan ignorant of international law and elementary reason of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It must not go unnoticed that the suppression of Chongryon by the Japanese reactionaries is timing to coincide with their hostile acts against the DPRK which are getting more malicious than ever before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These days they are running about like a headless chicken, openly crying for "sanctions and pressure" upon the DPRK, availing themselves of the U.S. hostile policy toward it. Things have come to such a pass that the Japanese ruling quarters and the group of the Liberal Democratic Party of Japan are letting loose an ugly torrent of outbursts urging hasty preparations for taking part in armed sanctions against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Far from honestly reflecting on and compensating for the past crimes, the Japanese are piling up crimes upon the crimes they have already committed, persisting in the moves against the DPRK and Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These moves can never be tolerated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should stop at once their foolish acts hostile to the DPRK and Chongryon, looking straight into the hatred for Japan rankling deeply in the hearts of the Korean people.

Kim Jong Il Provides Field Guidance to Chongjin
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il provided field guidance to the work related to the revolutionary sites in the city of Chongjin.
 He acquainted himself in detail about the management of the revolutionary sites and the education through them, going round the statue of President Kim Il Sung in Ranam District, the Malum Revolutionary Site and a room for the preservation and education in slogan-bearing trees. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed his satisfaction at the fact that the officials and other Party members and working people in the field of the preservation of revolutionary sites have established a perfect system for the eternal preservation of valuable historic relics and spruced up the sites while conducting the effective education in the revolutionary traditions among the people and the servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-Japanese forerunners covered thorny roads, crossing steep mountains and pulling through all sorts of ordeals under the guidance of Kim Il Sung, thus making a history of unprecedented resistance at the cost of their blood and sweat that won the admiration of the world people, he said, adding: The spirit of devotedly defending the leader and the indomitable revolutionary spirit displayed by the anti-Japanese guerrillas are now being inherited by our servicepersons and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the brilliant revolutionary traditions created by the President in the period of the long-drawn anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle serve as the strong roots of our Party and revolution, he said that the Korean revolution is winning victory after victory because these traditions of Juche are being steadfastly carried forward and developed generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The steady education in the revolutionary traditions conducted by our Party in the past helped our army and people bravely overcome unprecedented difficulties and unswervingly follow the road of revolution, he said, stressing that the strengthened education in the revolutionary traditions provides a fundamental guarantee for the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause pioneered by a leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He advanced important tasks which would serve as guidelines in managing the battle sites and intensifying the education through them, noting that the revolutionary sites are priceless treasures of the revolution and an important educational centre for arming all the Party members and other working people, the servicepersons and youth and children with the revolutionary traditions of our Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As there are in North Hamgyong Province many revolutionary sites, eternal treasures of our Party and people, the province should pay special attention to the preservation and management of those sites, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underlined the need for all the Party members and other working people to more thoroughly apply the revolutionary and fighting spirit and life style of the anti-Japanese guerillas to all aspects of work and life in steady response to the Party's slogan "Let us produce, study and live like the anti-Japanese guerrillas did!" and thus work miracles and perform exploits in the general advance of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Chief Secretary of the North Hamgyong Provincial Committee of the WPK Hong Sok Hyong, Secretary of the WPK Central Committee Kim Ki Nam, Department Director of the WPK Central Committee Pak Nam Gi.

Kim Jong Il Gives Field Guidance to Chongjin University of Mining and Metallurgy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 7 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave field guidance to Chongjin University of Mining and Metallurgy. 
 He went round a monument to the on-the-spot instructions given by President Kim Il Sung, a room for preserving revolutionary relics and a room devoted to the history of the university. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The university which was established on the personal initiative of the President and traversed a glorious path under his wise guidance has developed to be a centre for training dependable technical personnel, he said, noting that the undying revolutionary feats performed by the President will shine long with the history of the university. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went round the Science Exhibition of the university. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Making the rounds of exhibits for a long while, he acquainted himself in detail with the achievements made in the development of education and scientific researches. He was greatly satisfied to learn that the teachers and students of the university have done a lot of work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went round a room for information service, an e-library, a room for computer designing, a hall for scientific idea, a geology museum and other places of the university to learn about how education is conducted there. He praised the University for having created good environment to help its students acquire rich scientific knowledge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth highly important tasks which would serve as guidelines in education and scientific researches at the university. It is possible to rapidly develop the nation's science and technology under a long-term plan only when reserves for scientists and technicians are trained on a high level as required by the developing reality, he noted, adding that Chongjin University of Mining and Metallurgy has a very important mission and duty to perform in consolidating the foundation of the nation's independent national economy and giving fullest play to its potential. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 He also called on the teachers of the university to steadily improve and strengthen the education to train more talented scientists and technicians as required by the developing reality, always bearing in mind the intention of the Party to bring the nation's science and technology to the world's level as quickly as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to train students as able scientists and technicians required by the IT era it is necessary to establish Juche in education, combine education and practice, steadily improve the contents and quality of education and decisively strengthen the scientific and technological education in particular, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that by training an increasing number of scientists and technicians with a high level of technology in a brief span of time the university should settle issues now arising in making the national economy Juche-oriented, modern and scientific and, at the same time, actively explore new fields of science and technology which are of weighty importance in the development of the mining and metal industries in order to make a positive contribution to the rapid development of the nation's overall science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to develop science and technology as required by the new century, it is necessary to fully equip students with new knowledge of technology, he said, urging the university to conduct a brisk work to introduce advanced technology in close touch with scientific research institutions and other universities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing to the need to steadily expand the ranks of scientists and technicians, who should take the lead in building a scientifically and technologically strong country, in order to provide a scientific and technological guarantee for the high-pitched drive of the Korean people to accelerate the general march of the Songun revolution aimed at building a rich and powerful country, he called for reaching the high eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation by dint of science and technology as early as possible.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to bring about a fresh turn in the training of technical personnel it is necessary to provide ample conditions for education and scientific researches and pay deep attention to this work, he emphasized&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
